cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper deals with stylometric analysis of user-contributed text data in three different OSNs, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses privacy implications of the study, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves data mining and information retrieval techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the stylometric linkability across different OSNs, which could fall under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
